      • hasNext

        public boolean hasNext()
        Description copied from class: ImageIterator
        Queries whether there is another ImageCoordinate that has not yet been visited in the current Image. If this iterator was constructed on an image boxed with a region of interest, then this will check if there are more coordinates that have not been visited in that region of interest.
        Specified by:
        hasNext in interface java.util.Iterator<ImageCoordinate>
        Overrides:
        hasNext in class ImageIterator
        Returns:
        true if there are more coordinates that have not yet been visited, false otherwise.

      • next

        public ImageCoordinate next()
        Description copied from class: ImageIterator
        Gets the next coordinate in the ImageIterator's Image. If the Image is boxed with a region of interest, this will get the next coordinate in the region of interest. ImageIterator makes no guarantee as to the order in which coordinates will be visited, so do not rely on any ordering. In particular, the order in which coordinates are visited may not be the same as the order of the underlying byte array representation of the Image.
        Specified by:
        next in interface java.util.Iterator<ImageCoordinate>
        Overrides:
        next in class ImageIterator
        Returns:
        An ImageCoordinate that is the next location in the ImageIterator's Image.
